1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,210
[Beth] <i>We all need to come together.</i>

2
00:00:02,293 --> 00:00:04,004
<i>We're all in danger.</i>

3
00:00:04,379 --> 00:00:06,297
<i>Including our loved ones.</i>

4
00:00:06,381 --> 00:00:08,049
<i>We need to stop Edong.</i>

5
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:12,387
<i>Why is he doing this to us, Ma?</i>

6
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:14,389
<i>Even if he could be</i>
<i>innocent, it's still wrong!</i>

7
00:00:14,472 --> 00:00:16,766
<i>But it's over now, dear. You're safe now.</i>

8
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:18,309
<i>We're right here.</i>

9
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:19,394
<i>I'm sorry, Uncle.</i>

10
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:21,855
<i>Edong hurt you because of me.</i>

11
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:23,565
<i>Even for me, it's hard to predict</i>

12
00:00:23,648 --> 00:00:24,899
<i>Edong's next move.</i>

13
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:26,818
<i>At this point, anything is possible.</i>

14
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:28,403
<i>We all need to be careful.</i>

15
00:00:28,486 --> 00:00:30,113
<i>We're surrounded by villains.</i>

16
00:00:30,196 --> 00:00:31,781
<i>We're surrounded by evil.</i>

17
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:35,326
<i>We are surround by</i>
<i>people who want to punish,</i>

18
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:36,619
<i>torture, and scare us.</i>

19
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:38,246
<i>And I feel like we're just waiting</i>

20
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:40,081
<i>to see which one of them strikes first.</i>

21
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:42,625
<i>I'll destroy you and I'll make sure</i>

22
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:43,626
<i>you'll fucking pay!</i>

23
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:48,214
[Edong] <i>I won't stop</i>
<i>until I complete my mission.</i>

24
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:53,428
[foreboding music playing]

25
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:09,277
[foreboding music intensifies]

26
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:21,247
[music becomes sinister]

27
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:38,556
[sinister music continues]

28
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:41,017
[cane thudding]

29
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,560
[groans]

30
00:01:44,103 --> 00:01:49,526
[laughing, wheezing]

31
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:56,241
[whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]

32
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:01,371
[cane thudding]

33
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:10,547
[theme music playing]

34
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,284
[cicadas chirping]

35
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:23,077
It seems like we went to the internet cafe

36
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:25,747
just to talk about
that Edong's return to Amurao.

37
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:28,458
He's not that dumb
to still come here, right?

38
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:29,334
[scoffs]

39
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:31,586
Ms. Vangie deceived a lot of people again.

40
00:03:31,669 --> 00:03:33,504
The entirety of
Amurao is in shambles right now

41
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:34,756
- because of her fake news!
- It's true!

42
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:37,884
Jesus! Len! Don't go scaring us!

43
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:40,303
My brother saw Edong with his own eyes!

44
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,930
He kidnapped a child!

45
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:45,475
My bro is sure that he's just in the area.

46
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:47,185
Wandering about in Amurao.

47
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:50,688
We should've gone home earlier!

48
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:53,942
We might…
We might cross paths with Edong!

49
00:03:54,025 --> 00:03:55,109
Hey, stop it.

50
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,778
We're not in a horror movie, okay?

51
00:03:56,861 --> 00:03:58,154
Stop believing in--

52
00:03:58,238 --> 00:03:59,447
[can clunking]

53
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:05,078
- [electricity zapping]
- [eerie music playing]

54
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:07,163
Let's go home.

55
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:09,958
[grunts]

56
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,125
[cane thuds]

57
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:15,922
[cane thuds]

58
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:19,092
Do you guys hear that?

59
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:24,347
[electricity zapping]

60
00:04:24,722 --> 00:04:26,849
[thunder rumbles]

61
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:31,104
- [eerie music continues]
- [electricity zapping]

62
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:40,280
Good evening.

63
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:43,157
[all shrieking] Ahh!

64
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:48,288
[laughing maniacally]

65
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:55,878
[wheezing]

66
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:59,382
[laughing maniacally]

67
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:02,510
Kyle hasn't been appearing
in his wife's posts for a few months now.

68
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:05,221
[Marco] Here's more.

69
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:08,474
Maybe they've split up.

70
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:12,353
That's why his wife has no reason
to post about him anymore.

71
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:14,939
[sighs]

72
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:16,357
But what about his personal account?

73
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:20,570
Before, his face is all over it.

74
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,451
[Marco] He hasn't posted
anything about himself in three months.

75
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,120
This is just all about his restaurant.

76
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,247
He just suddenly disappeared.

77
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:34,125
You're right.

78
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:37,336
This could be a lead.

79
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:39,881
Is there…

80
00:05:39,964 --> 00:05:42,550
Someone in the US
you could ask for help with?

81
00:05:43,384 --> 00:05:44,677
Someone who knows him?

82
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:46,554
[dramatic music playing]

83
00:05:46,637 --> 00:05:48,056
Alice's mom.

84
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:50,683
She's in the US.

85
00:05:52,268 --> 00:05:54,020
According to your Auntie Erna,

86
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:57,440
no one's seen him for a few months now.

87
00:05:58,316 --> 00:06:00,902
Not in the community,
not even at the church.

88
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:06,532
Even those who know him
aren't sure if he's still in Texas.

89
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:09,702
Even his parents.

90
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:12,997
He's not there either.

91
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:16,876
[Alice] It's been around three months.

92
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:19,170
Kyle returned to the Philippines before

93
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:21,214
because he's involved in another problem.

94
00:06:21,839 --> 00:06:23,758
What if that's what happened again

95
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:26,052
so no one in the US knows where he is?

96
00:06:26,636 --> 00:06:27,929
[Mel sighs] So…

97
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:29,430
Do you think he's here?

98
00:06:30,431 --> 00:06:32,016
I'll go talk again to Kyle's mom.

99
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:35,144
Be careful when you talk to her.

100
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:36,729
- She might find out--
- [door opens]

101
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:44,654
[stirring music playing]

102
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:56,499
[music fades]

103
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:59,794
[PBI agent] <i>It's too dangerous</i>
<i>for the divers to continue the search.</i>

104
00:06:59,877 --> 00:07:02,922
<i>They also don't want to issue</i>
<i>a clearance because of the storm.</i>

105
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:05,466
It's why we haven't
returned yet since last week.

106
00:07:06,717 --> 00:07:08,136
[sighs] I understand.

107
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:11,639
Their families just want
an update on the search.

108
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:13,724
[PBI agent] <i>If our count is correct,</i>

109
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:16,394
we're missing one body

110
00:07:16,477 --> 00:07:19,480
<i>- compared to the missing beauty queens.</i>
- [uneasy music playing]

111
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:22,608
Are there any news on the DNA tests?

112
00:07:22,692 --> 00:07:23,860
<i>Anytime next week.</i>

113
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:26,070
We might be able to get the results.

114
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:28,197
And Oslo?

115
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:29,699
Did he finally fess up?

116
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:32,493
<i>Not yet, Attorney.</i>
<i>He's a tough one to crack.</i>

117
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:34,704
Still, we continue to grill him.

118
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:37,748
Alright, thank you. I'll just call again.

119
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:40,501
[music fades]

120
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:43,212
Are you okay?

121
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:48,092
[pensive music playing]

122
00:07:48,176 --> 00:07:50,136
Oslo still hasn't confessed.

123
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:55,641
He's just dragging it out
'til his master wakes up.

124
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,560
He'll reach his limit soon.

125
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,188
I hope so.

126
00:08:01,856 --> 00:08:04,025
[sighs sharply] Thank you for last night.

127
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:06,360
And sorry too.

128
00:08:07,403 --> 00:08:08,654
Was I too drunk?

129
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:12,783
[pensive music continues]

130
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:13,993
You don't remember?

131
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:17,163
No…

132
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,082
Why, did I do something embarrassing?

133
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:24,128
[pensive music continues]

134
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:25,171
[Erica grunts]

135
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:40,353
You didn't.

136
00:08:40,436 --> 00:08:44,982
[pensive music continues]

137
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:51,864
[breathes deeply] Uh…

138
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:54,992
I'll tell Alice that we're leaving.

139
00:08:56,786 --> 00:09:01,207
[pensive music continues]

140
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,417
[footsteps retreating]

141
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:08,923
[music fades]

142
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:10,424
[breathes heavily]

143
00:09:11,509 --> 00:09:13,469
We have a meeting with a prosecutor.

144
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:17,306
We have to prepare for the trial.

145
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:22,228
How are you?

146
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:24,522
[scoffs]

147
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,275
Nervous.

148
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:28,818
[scoffs, sighs]

149
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,445
Scared shitless.

150
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:36,242
How about you?

151
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:40,371
Don't tell me you're fine, Lucas.

152
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:41,998
[exhales deeply]

153
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:44,625
If you've been drinking 'til
you don't remember a thing,

154
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:46,752
you're not okay.

155
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,428
I heard you two. [inhales sharply]

156
00:09:57,847 --> 00:09:59,640
I'm still trying to face everything.

157
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,310
I kept calling you last night.

158
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,396
I might've been knocked out already.

159
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:06,814
With Erica.

160
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:10,359
She was just the first person to see me

161
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:13,446
and was kind
enough to take me to my hotel.

162
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:20,870
You know that I'm here whenever
you need someone to talk to, right?

163
00:10:24,915 --> 00:10:26,000
But…

164
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:30,004
I don't want to be a burden to you.

165
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,173
What?

166
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:35,593
That's not like that to me.

167
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:38,095
[somber music playing]

168
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:39,764
Talking with you means,

169
00:10:40,431 --> 00:10:42,350
I get to talk to someone too.

170
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:46,812
Honestly, Lucas, out of everyone,

171
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:50,066
you are the only one
who understands what I'm going through.

172
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:52,276
[exhales heavily]

173
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,403
[somber music continues]

174
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:55,738
[inhales sharply]

175
00:10:55,821 --> 00:10:57,740
I feel so lost, Lucas.

176
00:10:58,449 --> 00:11:00,743
[sniffles, crying]

177
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:02,912
I'm trying so hard to be strong.

178
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,081
But…

179
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:07,541
It's as if I'm on the edge of a cliff,

180
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:11,170
standing, and I could fall at any time.

181
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:13,881
And it's been like that for a while.

182
00:11:15,591 --> 00:11:16,926
Until you came along.

183
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,552
[sobs]

184
00:11:20,221 --> 00:11:22,181
And for the first time,

185
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:26,394
I felt like I had something to hold onto.

186
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:30,189
[somber music continues]

187
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:31,440
[sobs]

188
00:11:35,528 --> 00:11:37,822
I need that now, Lucas.

189
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:43,119
[crying] Someone to hold on to.

190
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:47,331
[gentle music playing]

191
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:56,590
Like I told you, Mel.

192
00:11:58,634 --> 00:12:00,302
- [Mel sniffles]
- If you ever need help,

193
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:02,138
I'm right here, just tell me.

194
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:09,520
I'm so glad that you're
fighting for yourself now.

195
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:11,355
[chuckles]

196
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:16,569
I went through the same with my father
so I know how hard it is.

197
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:19,363
Even now.

198
00:12:20,698 --> 00:12:22,074
I still think…

199
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:25,327
[gentle music continues]

200
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:27,580
…I wish my mother had a chance.

201
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:29,748
[quivers]

202
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:32,626
To be free and to fight just like you.

203
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:37,798
[sniffles]

204
00:12:37,882 --> 00:12:40,217
[gentle music continues]

205
00:12:40,301 --> 00:12:42,178
You'll be free from Anton soon.

206
00:12:44,013 --> 00:12:45,639
You'll get through this.

207
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:50,269
And I'll be right
here if you need any help.

208
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:52,938
[sniffling]

209
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:57,276
[gentle music continues]

210
00:12:58,402 --> 00:12:59,904
[gentle music fades]

211
00:12:59,987 --> 00:13:02,573
[man] Where are my slippers?

212
00:13:02,656 --> 00:13:06,535
- Ga, did you see my glasses?
- Maybe it's just there.

213
00:13:07,953 --> 00:13:10,956
[man grunts] What about my cane?

214
00:13:11,415 --> 00:13:16,587
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [Edong groaning softly]

215
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,886
Edward, the delivery

216
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:27,431
of donations at healing mass in Santa Fe,
we'll take care of them.

217
00:13:28,265 --> 00:13:30,726
- We'll rent a van for now.
- [Edward scoffs]

218
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:33,354
What are you saying? Why?

219
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:36,815
Why spend money when my van's there?

220
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:40,152
Besides, I can handle it.

221
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:43,656
[pensive music playing]

222
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:46,158
We're just worried
about you and Christina,

223
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:48,369
after what happened to you.

224
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:51,163
We don't want to add to your worries.

225
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:52,540
[man] It's embarrassing, too.

226
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:55,251
You're the church leader, yet you're still

227
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:57,962
the one taking care of
deliveries and everything.

228
00:13:58,045 --> 00:13:59,171
[chuckles]

229
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:02,800
That's nothing to me.
Besides, I like what I'm doing.

230
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:08,097
Really, this was my vow, even when
Christina's parents were still alive.

231
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:11,809
I'm continuing it as a thank
you to them for accepting me.

232
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:15,020
And one more thing,
shouldn't we still continue

233
00:14:15,104 --> 00:14:17,439
with our vows even
when faced with hardship?

234
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:22,319
Because that's how
we'll know how strong we are.

235
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,655
You're really different, Edward.

236
00:14:25,906 --> 00:14:28,200
Just a little more,
and you could be a saint.

237
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:29,660
[Edward laughs]

238
00:14:29,743 --> 00:14:33,622
You, guys, really.
I just do what I can, okay?

239
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:36,458
- Eat first.
- Thank you.

240
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:37,751
Alright, thank you. You should eat, too.

241
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:38,752
Eat a lot, okay?

242
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:44,800
- [Edong grunting softly]
- [unsettling music playing]

243
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:53,100
[music becomes suspenseful]

244
00:14:55,769 --> 00:14:57,271
[Edong grunts]

245
00:14:57,354 --> 00:14:59,690
- Check the other areas.
- [Police] Okay, sir.

246
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:02,776
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning, too, grandpa.

247
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:04,778
- Take care.
- You too.

248
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:11,327
[suspenseful music intensifies]

249
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:26,133
- [Edong laughing softly]
- [suspenseful music continues]

250
00:15:29,345 --> 00:15:33,682
- [cane thuds softly]
- [Edong laughing softly]

251
00:15:34,516 --> 00:15:36,936
[suspenseful music crescendos]

252
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:40,481
[Alba] Alright, ladies.
Based on what you've submitted,

253
00:15:40,981 --> 00:15:43,651
we've got a buffet of criminal charges.

254
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:45,527
And as for Anton,

255
00:15:46,278 --> 00:15:49,865
he will be served a full
course meal of accountability.

256
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:52,368
Mrs. Montenegro, as the wife,

257
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:55,454
you have grounds
for battery, assault, injury,

258
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:56,914
psychological abuse,

259
00:15:56,997 --> 00:16:01,502
the Anti-Violence Against Women
and Their Children Act or VAWC.

260
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:03,879
Sorry. That acronym.

261
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:06,382
[lips smack] It's better than G&G.

262
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,551
Attorney Melendez…

263
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:12,388
I wouldn't have had the privilege

264
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:14,056
of meeting such a fierce lawyer

265
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:16,058
if Anton killed
you with that strangulation.

266
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:18,686
And that asshole struck you with a pipe!

267
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:21,522
- [blows landing]
- [Erica] Argh! Argh! Argh!

268
00:16:22,606 --> 00:16:25,985
Now, what case are we filing against him,

269
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:27,861
and what is your justification?

270
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:30,948
- Attempted homicide.
- [tense music playing]

271
00:16:31,031 --> 00:16:32,408
He had an intent to kill.

272
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:36,286
The pipe strike to the head
and the choking, clearly show intent.

273
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:38,163
[Erica gasping for air]

274
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:39,623
Exactly.

275
00:16:39,707 --> 00:16:43,210
He missed the kill. But we won't.

276
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:45,337
[Alba] Mrs. Mora…

277
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:47,798
I'll file the same case

278
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:50,259
because we both almost died there.

279
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:54,513
Well, you have defensive wounds…

280
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:55,973
- [Beth] <i>Let me go! Argh!</i>
- [kick landing]

281
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:58,058
- [grunts]
- [groans]

282
00:16:58,142 --> 00:17:00,936
…mild concussion. He attacked you, yes.

283
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,313
But he didn't intend to kill you, so,

284
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:06,567
yours is less serious physical injuries.

285
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:07,609
Oh.

286
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:10,529
[tense music continues]

287
00:17:11,572 --> 00:17:12,781
What about me?

288
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:16,785
[tense music continues]

289
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:21,915
[Artillero] Of course,
we will push for dismissal.

290
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:24,501
But we have to be willing to fight.

291
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:29,006
Their biggest mistake?
Was what Alice did to you.

292
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:31,300
[tense music continues]

293
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:34,553
Attorney, do we have a good chance?

294
00:17:34,636 --> 00:17:36,972
We will file
a hyper-aggressive countercharge

295
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:39,099
for attempted
homicide against Alice Miller.

296
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:42,102
The use of a hard object,
a glass bottle…

297
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,645
[glass breaks, clinks]

298
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:46,565
[Artillero] …struck against the head,
which is a vital part of the body,

299
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:49,943
suggests intent
to kill or seriously wound.

300
00:17:50,027 --> 00:17:53,238
We will argue that this
was not mere self-defense,

301
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:55,532
but an unlawful, calculated,

302
00:17:55,616 --> 00:17:57,743
and disproportionate act of violence.

303
00:17:58,535 --> 00:18:02,081
This puts their main
rescuer in immediate legal jeopardy

304
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:04,249
for a non-bailable offense.

305
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:06,710
It will fracture their little truth.

306
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:08,253
[music fades]

307
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,339
[Alice] Can Anton sue me?

308
00:18:11,465 --> 00:18:13,675
[unsettling music playing]

309
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,177
[sighs]

310
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:18,806
You are not the criminal, darling.

311
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:22,101
You are the plot twist.

312
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:24,770
- And you did what a woman should do
- [music becomes dramatic]

313
00:18:24,853 --> 00:18:27,689
when a monster attacks her.

314
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:28,982
You fought back.

315
00:18:29,066 --> 00:18:31,652
[Alba] Classic
self-defense under Article 11.

316
00:18:31,735 --> 00:18:34,238
No liability. But your testimony…

317
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:37,241
…is our secret weapon.

318
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:38,909
[relieved sigh]

319
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:40,619
[Alba] Attorney Melendez…

320
00:18:41,411 --> 00:18:44,373
with the multiple charges
and the sheer volume of evidence,

321
00:18:44,456 --> 00:18:47,209
what is your take on
the most effective way

322
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:48,877
to prosecute the cases?

323
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,714
We file separate cases for each of us.

324
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:54,299
Attempted homicide for me,

325
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:56,593
less serious physical injuries for Beth…

326
00:18:57,052 --> 00:18:59,263
And no charges for Alice

327
00:18:59,346 --> 00:19:01,640
'cause it was clearly
an act of self-defense.

328
00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:04,893
But we move
to consolidate them in one trial.

329
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:06,645
Meaning?

330
00:19:06,728 --> 00:19:09,731
Meaning, separate
counts of crime for Anton,

331
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:12,401
but there's only one trial, one judge,

332
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:14,570
and one set of witnesses and evidence.

333
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:17,239
[Alba] One demon, multiple crimes.

334
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:19,408
Most efficient, most powerful.

335
00:19:19,491 --> 00:19:22,202
That pins Anton not just a one-time jerk,

336
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:24,997
but a repeat
offender with a signature style.

337
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:29,293
And judges love patterns,
and they hate predators

338
00:19:29,376 --> 00:19:31,753
- who think they're clever.
- [music fades]

339
00:19:31,837 --> 00:19:34,673
[Artillero] Next,
we erase the rescue narrative,

340
00:19:34,756 --> 00:19:38,844
and replace it with
pre-meditated ambush and assault.

341
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:40,762
[tense music playing]

342
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:42,014
How?

343
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:43,891
Your wife deliberately lured you

344
00:19:43,974 --> 00:19:46,351
to the isolated area of the coffee shop

345
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:47,853
using a phone call.

346
00:19:47,936 --> 00:19:50,689
Because she knew her friends were close,

347
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:51,982
she set you up.

348
00:19:52,649 --> 00:19:54,234
We will file countercharges

349
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:57,196
for less serious or
serious physical injuries

350
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:58,697
against Erica and Beth.

351
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:02,409
This forces all
the women to face jail time,

352
00:20:02,492 --> 00:20:04,661
not just be complainants.

353
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:06,997
What we will show is that

354
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:10,042
the heroism of women that they're stating

355
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:12,502
was actually a conspiracy to hurt you.

356
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,963
What about the coffee shop owner?

357
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:16,340
Isn't she a witness?

358
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:18,550
All she saw was the aftermath.

359
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,594
She did not witness the whole thing,

360
00:20:20,677 --> 00:20:22,012
not even their CCTV

361
00:20:22,095 --> 00:20:24,473
because, in the first place,
they didn't have any.

362
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:26,808
[tense music crescendos]

363
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,810
[Alba] Now for the kicker,
Mrs. Montenegro.

364
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:30,687
Your VAWC case is separate.

365
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:32,773
It will fall under the family court.

366
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:35,150
Different playground, different rules,

367
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:38,403
different prosecutor. It's a deeper look.

368
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:42,491
Physical, emotional,
psychological, financial, economic,

369
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,868
The whole pattern of abuse,

370
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:47,788
so we can paint the whole ugly picture.

371
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:49,456
And speaking of family court,

372
00:20:49,539 --> 00:20:52,584
that is where you will
file for protective order.

373
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:56,088
[Alba] Attorney Melendez,
why is it crucial

374
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:58,924
to get a temporary protection order,

375
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:02,219
and what immediate
win does it give your friend?

376
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:06,682
The TPO is a non-negotiable legal mandate
for immediate safety.

377
00:21:06,765 --> 00:21:10,394
The biggest win here is the
exclusive possession of the conjugal home.

378
00:21:10,477 --> 00:21:13,689
And family court can
immediately issue a protective order

379
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:16,400
within 24 hours
without even talking to Anton.

380
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:17,985
She's right, Mel.

381
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:21,029
A TPO can legally
evict Anton from your home

382
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,864
regardless of who owns it.

383
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:26,285
Because under the law,
your safety is the priority.

384
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:30,205
It stops any form
of financial violence or economic abuse.

385
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:33,750
The TPO can restrict Anton
from accessing his bank accounts,

386
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:36,920
especially your common
bank accounts or properties,

387
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:40,382
so he can't drain your joint accounts
or sell your assets.

388
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:43,260
Now, onto the strategy.

389
00:21:43,343 --> 00:21:46,972
You have two choices on
how to proceed with the prosecution.

390
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:50,726
One, we prosecute all
cases at the same time,

391
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:51,935
double court drama.

392
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:56,189
Or two,
win the collective criminals cases first,

393
00:21:56,273 --> 00:22:01,236
and use that win
to beat Anton in your VAWC case.

394
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:06,033
[dramatic music playing]

395
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,369
What do you think?

396
00:22:10,203 --> 00:22:13,248
Well, that depends on
what you can handle, Mel.

397
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:15,292
But personally,

398
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:17,794
option two's one-two punch is clean.

399
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:22,341
But with the slow pace
of getting justice in this country…

400
00:22:23,216 --> 00:22:24,301
Right.

401
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,762
We'll file the cases at the same time.

402
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:29,723
And I want Attorney Erica to defend me.

403
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:31,308
[dramatic music continues]

404
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:34,811
Look at that. Instant dream team.

405
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:40,108
Unfortunately, ladies,
I am the lead public prosecutor.

406
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:42,611
But with your consent,

407
00:22:42,694 --> 00:22:45,238
she can be a private prosecutor

408
00:22:45,322 --> 00:22:46,740
under my supervision.

409
00:22:47,449 --> 00:22:49,868
Like a co-counsel?

410
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:53,705
I'm the general,
she's the field commander.

411
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:56,166
[Alba] She will help
you with everything you need.

412
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:59,711
Getting affidavit,
evidence, prepping for testimony.

413
00:22:59,795 --> 00:23:03,006
Everything you need
before the battle begins.

414
00:23:03,090 --> 00:23:04,716
[dramatic music continues]

415
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:07,969
Now, let's make sure

416
00:23:08,053 --> 00:23:12,808
Anton Montenegro
regrets that he touched any of you.

417
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:15,852
[Artillero] Finally, the PR strategy.

418
00:23:15,936 --> 00:23:18,146
We control the narrative.

419
00:23:18,897 --> 00:23:21,483
Anton, you are the betrayed husband.

420
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:24,027
We will secure a psychological evaluation,

421
00:23:24,111 --> 00:23:26,613
and strategically leak portions of it,

422
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:28,949
claiming that you are suffering

423
00:23:29,032 --> 00:23:32,119
from anxiety, depression, or PTSD

424
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:35,997
due to your wife's infidelity,
and them attacking you.

425
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:39,292
We will argue, your rage was a result

426
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:42,462
of a powerful and blinding fit of passion,

427
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:45,590
making the VAWC
case look like a distraction

428
00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:47,467
from Mel's own betrayal.

429
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:50,637
I like that.

430
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:55,350
[dramatic music continues]

431
00:23:55,433 --> 00:23:58,436
It is important that you
just keep doing what you're doing.

432
00:23:58,937 --> 00:24:01,523
Keep talking about
your heartbreak and the affair,

433
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:05,277
but do not say anything
aggressive against the women.

434
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:09,573
We must subtly paint Mel, Erica, and Beth

435
00:24:09,656 --> 00:24:12,075
as a powerful and vicious group of women

436
00:24:12,159 --> 00:24:14,536
who are ganging up against a good man.

437
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:17,747
If we control the narrative,

438
00:24:18,498 --> 00:24:21,751
we show the court
there is reasonable doubt.

439
00:24:26,173 --> 00:24:27,090
That's easy.

440
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:31,803
[dramatic music continues]

441
00:24:49,237 --> 00:24:50,697
[music fades]

442
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:54,492
<i>Ever since Edong showed up,</i>
<i>everything has changed.</i>

443
00:24:54,576 --> 00:24:56,912
<i>I'm scared that he might be the reason</i>

444
00:24:56,995 --> 00:24:59,206
<i>why you and Dad will have to break up.</i>

445
00:24:59,289 --> 00:25:01,041
<i>I'm sure you're wondering</i>

446
00:25:01,124 --> 00:25:03,043
<i>how he and I came to have an affair.</i>

447
00:25:03,126 --> 00:25:05,837
<i>I don't own him, Mel.</i>
<i>And, besides, that's done.</i>

448
00:25:05,921 --> 00:25:07,631
<i>But I don't want it to be over.</i>

449
00:25:07,714 --> 00:25:11,051
<i>Are you sure it's okay for you</i>
<i>to take care of your Auntie Christina?</i>

450
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:12,969
<i>There's police outside.</i>

451
00:25:13,053 --> 00:25:15,555
<i>He'd be stupid to come back here, right?</i>
